rComments: The prof would not explain the final exam format and also she didn't have the final review as other courses. The lecture slides is not enough for your review. She provided tons of the information in class. Attendance and focus is required in this course

I've taken every single course taught by Mandy, ranging from first year to fourth year courses. I have gotten 4.0 on all her courses. She is extremely caring and gives great lectures. Her exams are extremely fair and straight forward. Her courses require studying but they are not too difficult.

She is a kind person, but her class is just tough!! It makes me like a fool as I worked hard and get 1/5, 3/5 in quizzes and the tests ruined my gpa...I hope I can, in my life, get a past exam or something. But the truth is, no guidance and I need to face my fate in exams.

Meriano doesn't provide much information on upcoming assignments because she wants us to figure it out on our own. Her helpfulness is basically non-existent, her outlines are vague and her lectures were boring. She also LOVES group work, be prepared to be riddled with group discussions . She's a nice professor but in terms of guidance... not much.
Drop Drop Drop, poor professor, doesn't care about students. Assignments are ambiguous but marked hard. If i could drop it I would. Doesn't help students, lectures are useless. Memorize the book
Really good prof/hydrogeologist knows material well,  very helpful and always wants the best for her students

I can't rate "zero"!!! She is rude. She doesn't even know how to use email! Her lectures are extremely boring, and lecture notes are almost useless. She can't explain concepts properly, but her exam is hard like hell. If u get her, drop the class immediately!
if you pay attention in lecture, you should do well.  poster assignments were kind of a freebie.
